explanation: This solution works by first counting the occurrences of each character in the string. It then counts the number of characters that appear an odd number of times. A string can be divided into k palindromes if and only if at most k-1 characters appear an odd number of times. This is because each palindrome can have at most one character that appears an odd number of times, and the remaining characters must appear an even number of times.

